{"parse":{"title":"Pohlke's theorem","pageid":52991874,"revid":787520193,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Pohlke's theorem</b> is the fundamental theorem of <a href=\"/wiki/Axonometry\" title=\"Axonometry\">axonometry</a>. It was established 1853 by the German painter and teacher of <a href=\"/wiki/Descriptive_geometry\" title=\"Descriptive geometry\">descriptive geometry</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Karl_Wilhelm_Pohlke\" title=\"Karl Wilhelm Pohlke\">Karl Wilhelm Pohlke</a>. The first proof of the theorem was published 1864 by the German mathematician <a href=\"/wiki/Hermann_Amandus_Schwarz\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hermann Amandus Schwarz\">Hermann Amandus Schwarz</a>, who was a student of Pohlke. Therefore the theorem is sometimes called <b>theorem of Pohlke and Schwarz</b>, too.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#The_theorem\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The theorem</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Application_to_axonometry\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Application to axonometry</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Remarks_on_Schwarz&#39;s_proof\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Remarks on Schwarz's proof</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_theorem\">The theorem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pohlke%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: The theorem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Axonom-pohlke.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Axonom-pohlke.svg/220px-Axonom-pohlke.svg.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"223\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Axonom-pohlke.svg/330px-Axonom-pohlke.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Axonom-pohlke.svg/440px-Axonom-pohlke.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"373\" data-file-height=\"378\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Axonom-pohlke.svg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Pohlke's theorem</div></div></div>\n<ul><li>Three arbitrary line sections <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}{\\overline {U}},{\\overline {O}}{\\overline {V}},{\\overline {O}}{\\overline {W}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>O</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>U</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>O</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>V</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>O</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>W</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}{\\overline {U}},{\\overline {O}}{\\overline {V}},{\\overline {O}}{\\overline {W}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c4a24f21d4389b73dd35808be1b7bf887ce2a0d7\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:14.647ex; height:3.343ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}{\\overline {U}},{\\overline {O}}{\\overline {V}},{\\overline {O}}{\\overline {W}}}\"/></span> in a plane originating at point <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>O</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3bbd5bb1b148dda3be9d95bcd36f21cc909b59c8\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.888ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}}\"/></span>, which are not contained in a line, can be considered as the <a href=\"/wiki/Parallel_projection\" title=\"Parallel projection\">parallel projection</a> of three edges <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle OU,OV,OW}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>O</mi>\n        <mi>U</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mi>O</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mi>O</mi>\n        <mi>W</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle OU,OV,OW}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6566030bc610fc279d3405b074627be4e331d9d3\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:13.393ex; height:2.509ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle OU,OV,OW}\"/></span> of a <a href=\"/wiki/Cube\" title=\"Cube\">cube</a>.</li></ul>\n<p>For a mapping of a unit cube, one has to apply an additional scaling either in the space or in the plane. Because a parallprojection and a scaling preserves ratios one can map an arbitrary point <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle P=(x,y,z)}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mi>y</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mi>z</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle P=(x,y,z)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7a1320b61607963c1f2ae3598093f6167d7e0ed6\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:12.294ex; height:2.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle P=(x,y,z)}\"/></span> by the axonometric procedure below.\n</p><p>Pohlke's theorem can be stated in terms of linear algebra as:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Any <a href=\"/wiki/Affine_transformation\" title=\"Affine transformation\">affine mapping</a> of the 3-dimesional space onto a plane can be considered as the composition of a <a href=\"/wiki/Similarity_(geometry)\" title=\"Similarity (geometry)\">similarity</a> and a parallel projection.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Application_to_axonometry\">Application to axonometry</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pohlke%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Application to axonometry\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Axonom-def.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Axonom-def.svg/220px-Axonom-def.svg.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"241\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Axonom-def.svg/330px-Axonom-def.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Axonom-def.svg/440px-Axonom-def.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"372\" data-file-height=\"407\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Axonom-def.svg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>the principle of axonometric projection</div></div></div>\n<p>Pohlke's theorem is the justification for the following easy procedure to construct a scaled parallel projection of a 3-dimensional object using coordinates,:<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ol><li>Choose the images of the coordinate axes, not contained in a line.</li>\n<li>Choose for any coordinate axis forshortenings <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle v_{x},v_{y},v_{z}&gt;0.}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>y</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>z</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&gt;</mo>\n        <mn>0.</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle v_{x},v_{y},v_{z}&gt;0.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/41dcfdba5cce09ca95c737e0fce6bfdc2cc6ad2a\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:13.582ex; height:2.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle v_{x},v_{y},v_{z}&gt;0.}\"/></span></li>\n<li>The image <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {P}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>P</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\overline {P}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d5e1bed5bc42d4e46dd9e5c7d2fc327927b87169\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.025ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {P}}}\"/></span> of a point <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle P=(x,y,z)}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mi>y</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mi>z</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle P=(x,y,z)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7a1320b61607963c1f2ae3598093f6167d7e0ed6\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:12.294ex; height:2.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle P=(x,y,z)}\"/></span> is determined by the three steps, starting at point <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>O</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3bbd5bb1b148dda3be9d95bcd36f21cc909b59c8\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.888ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {O}}}\"/></span>:</li></ol>\n<dl><dd><dl><dd>go <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle v_{x}\\cdot x}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \u22c5 --></mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle v_{x}\\cdot x}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e9265fb1196fbc6eee24f2f6d89a20b0beb82eda\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:5.309ex; height:2.009ex;\" alt=\"v_x\\cdot x\"/></span> in <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {x}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\overline {x}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9fa4039bbc2a0048c3a3c02e5fd24390cab0dc97\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.445ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"{\\overline {x}}\"/></span>-direction, then</dd>\n<dd>go <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle v_{y}\\cdot y}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>y</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \u22c5 --></mo>\n        <mi>y</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle v_{y}\\cdot y}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2fdedfa7d615250c552fb9956844038562108356\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:5.012ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"v_y\\cdot y\"/></span> in <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {y}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>y</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\overline {y}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/fca7adf9164266bae2b7a13f09a953c43d23d7b7\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:1.281ex; height:2.676ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {y}}}\"/></span>-direction, then</dd>\n<dd>go <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle v_{z}\\cdot z}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>z</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \u22c5 --></mo>\n        <mi>z</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle v_{z}\\cdot z}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c06c38cbdd303c316e9e4da2e33aab0c69782785\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:4.897ex; height:2.009ex;\" alt=\"v_z\\cdot z\"/></span> in <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {z}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>z</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\overline {z}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/64281d029a1d4bef9545644f01821c713f876f76\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.208ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"{\\overline {z}}\"/></span>-direction and</dd></dl></dd>\n<dd>4. mark the point as <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {P}}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mover>\n            <mi>P</mi>\n            <mo accent=\"false\">&#x00AF;<!-- \u00af --></mo>\n          </mover>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\overline {P}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d5e1bed5bc42d4e46dd9e5c7d2fc327927b87169\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.025ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\overline {P}}}\"/></span>.</dd></dl>\n<p>In order to get undistorted pictures, one has to choose the images of the axes and the forshortenings carefully (see <a href=\"/wiki/Axonometry\" title=\"Axonometry\">Axonometry</a>). In order to get an <a href=\"/wiki/Orthographic_projection\" title=\"Orthographic projection\">orthographic projection</a> only the images of the axes are free and the forshortenings are determined. (see <a href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/orthogonale_Axonometrie\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"de:orthogonale Axonometrie\">de:orthogonale Axonometrie</a>).\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Remarks_on_Schwarz.27s_proof\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Remarks_on_Schwarz's_proof\">Remarks on Schwarz's proof</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pohlke%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Remarks on Schwarz&#039;s proof\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Schwarz formulated and proved the more general statement:\n</p>\n<ul><li>The vertices of any <a href=\"/wiki/Quadrilateral\" title=\"Quadrilateral\">quadrilateral</a> can be considered as an oblique parallel projection of the vertices of a <a href=\"/wiki/Tetrahedron\" title=\"Tetrahedron\">tetrahedron</a> that is <a href=\"/wiki/Similarity_(geometry)\" title=\"Similarity (geometry)\">similar</a> to a given tetrahedron.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>and used a theorem of <a href=\"/wiki/Lhuilier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lhuilier\">L\u2019Huilier</a>: \n</p>\n<ul><li>Every triangle can be considered as the orthographic projection of a triangle of a given shape.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pohlke%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">G. Pickert: <i>Vom Satz von Pohlke zur linearen Algebra</i>, Didaktik der Mathematik 11 (1983), 4, pp. 297\u2013306.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Ulrich Graf, Martin Barner: <i>Darstellende Geometrie.</i> Quelle &amp; Meyer, Heidelberg 1961, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/3-494-00488-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/3-494-00488-9\">3-494-00488-9</a>, p.144.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Roland St\u00e4rk: <i>Darstellende Geometrie</i>, Sch\u00f6ningh, 1978, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/3-506-37443-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/3-506-37443-5\">3-506-37443-5</a>, p.156.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Sklen\u00e1rikov\u00e1, Zita; P\u00e9mov\u00e1, Marta (2007). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://math.unipa.it/~grim/quad17_sklenarikova-pemova_07.pdf\">\"The Pohlke\u2013Schwarz Theorem and its Relevancy in the Didactics of Mathematics\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>Quaderni di Ricerca in Didattica</i>. G.R.I.M. (Department of Mathematics, University of Palermo, Italy) (17): 155.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Quaderni+di+Ricerca+in+Didattica&amp;rft.atitle=The+Pohlke%E2%80%93Schwarz+Theorem+and+its+Relevancy+in+the+Didactics+of+Mathematics&amp;rft.issue=17&amp;rft.pages=155&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.aulast=Sklen%C3%A1rikov%C3%A1&amp;rft.aufirst=Zita&amp;rft.au=P%C3%A9mov%C3%A1%2C+Marta&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmath.unipa.it%2F~grim%2Fquad17_sklenarikova-pemova_07.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APohlke%27s+theorem\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pohlke%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Karl_Pohlke\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Karl Pohlke\">K. Pohlke</a>: <i>Zehn Tafeln zur darstellenden Geometrie.</i> Gaertner-Verlag, Berlin 1876 <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=V17kAAAAMAAJ&amp;dq=Karl+Pohlke&amp;source=gbs_navlinks_s\">(Google Books.)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hermann_Schwarz\" title=\"Hermann Schwarz\">Schwarz, H. A.</a>:<i>Elementarer Beweis des Pohlkeschen Fundamentalsatzes der Axonometrie</i>,J. reine angew. Math. 63, 309\u2013314, 1864.</li>\n<li>Arnold Emch: <i>Proof of Pohlke's Theorem and Its Generalizations by Affinity</i>, American Journal of Mathematics, Vol. 40, No. 4 (Oct., 1918), pp.&#160;366\u2013374</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pohlke%27s_theorem&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https: